  "text": "Treatment of Type II endoleaks by way of prevention is cited in various reports [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This is theoretically achieved with prophylactic embolization of arterial branches and collaterals that may ultimately lead to a Type II endoleak following EVAR. The most common example of this is pre-EVAR embolization of the internal iliac artery (Figure 4 ) [CITATION_4] . This can be performed in a staged fashion, or immediately prior to EVAR during the same operation, and is often a useful adjunct when intending to treat both aortic and common iliac artery aneurysms when an iliac branched device is not indicated or suitable for the iliac artery anatomy.",
